Apollo is a set of tools and a community-driven effort to help developers use GraphQL in their applications. It is best known for its client and server implementations, which simplify the process of integrating GraphQL into various environments. The Apollo Client is a state management library that enables applications to interact with a GraphQL API efficiently, while Apollo Server is a production-ready, spec-compliant GraphQL server that integrates easily with various backend technologies. Apollo also provides additional tools for caching, real-time data subscriptions, and performance monitoring, making it one of the most popular GraphQL solutions in modern development.

GraphQL has become a popular API standard due to its flexibility, optimized data fetching, and seamless integration with various technologies. More and more companies are adopting it as a modern solution in their systems.
